ont><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Why do casters need balancing?</span><hr size=1> I hear all this talk of caster balancing and such. Forgive me for my slowness on picking up on these things (thats my way).<br>
<br>
One question I could not find the answer to was: why?<br>
<br>
Why do casters need &quot;balancing&quot;.<br>
<br>
I have been very happy with my wizard and have not really come across any major issue that made me think the class was &quot;unbalalnced&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
So why are we unbalanced and what should be done about it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uayralin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ayralin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 12:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do casters need balancing?</span><hr size=1> Have you played a melee or grouped with one with others hits on?<br>
<br>
Any half-decent equipped melee class can significantly outdamage wizards over an extended fight, due to the constraints wizards face with a limited mana pool with which they deal their damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzerub.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zerub</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1203<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 12:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do casters need balancing?</span><hr size=1> Start a new wizard.<br>
<br>
Get to level 10.<br>
<br>
Ask for a group in EC.<br>
<br>
Get laughed at and told to go to hell.<br>
<br>
Level up to 20. Ask for a group at Sarnak Fort in loio.<br>
<br>
Get laughed at and told go to hell.<br>
<br>
<br>
Repeat these steps...over...and over...and over.<br>
<br>
Our sustained DPS in group situations as compared to a melee with Wurmslayer/centi weapons is absolutely horrible. We are not seen as attractive for ANY reasons to groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udanenel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1013<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 12:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do casters need balancing?</span><hr size=1> I can take a WurmSlayer and Centi LS, a full set if Crustacean Plate Mail and twink out a L1 Ogre Warrior.<br>
<br>
You twink out a L1 wizard with everything you can think of... who does more damage? Not even freaking close... The tank can out damage the wizard.<br>
<br>
Thats the &lt; 50 argument.<br>
<br>
The &gt; 50 argument is on a major mob with +150,000 HP, the fight begins and the wizards unloads for massive damage, then goes oom. The tanks steadily keep fighting and dealing their constant damage. The wizard meds to full and unloads again... the warrior keeps going.<br>
<br>
Do did more damage at the end of the fight? The tanks.<br>
<br>
Its even worse if you compare the damage a wizard can do to an epic rogue who constantly backstabs.<br>
<br>
Show me a wizard item that gives mana regen equal to a fungi tunics HP regen ... for 40kpp (approx cost of fungis).... doesn't exist.<br>
<br>
Casters do need tuning to deal equal amounts of damage that melee do... but that makes the assumption that verant ever thinks casters should equal even roughly, melee damage output.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
