<br>
I for one have never understood why everybody equates mana to Hp's.  Mana should equate to Melee stamina.  Don't get me wrong, I am not asking for a Nerf here, I just think that will be the ONLY way to ever bring caster and Melee into true balance, Equal downtime.  Downtime in groups is not decided by Melee ever, the caster calls downtime.  Whether that be Healer or Nuker is irrelevant.<br>
<br>
Even on the Rare occasions when Melee completely drains their stamina, they sit, and 10 seconds later they are back to Full Stamina and ready to fight again.  Or one of the Healer types casts a Stamina Refresh spell on the Melee completely filling their stamina bar again.  Which brings it right back to Caster mana causing the downtime, not any downtime of the melee. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udryfft.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dryfft</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 1:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> That is absurd.  A melee does damage with weapons not hitpoints.<br>
