I don't understand why it wasn't done this way from the beginning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushimone.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shimone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 1:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> /boggle.  My warrior soloes all the time with 0 yellow in his sta bar (he has 204 sta or so) and it does NOTHING.  And whoever said that warriors don't come to a screeching halt is wrong as well.  My said warrior alt can solo 2-3 blue mobs before getting to the point where he either has to A) bandage to 50% (after which point soloing becomes kinda dangerous), B) beg a heal/regen, or C) sit his ass down for hours at a time waiting for hps to regen on their own.  Verdict?  Warriors can't solo for long periods of time to ANYWHERE near the effect that wizards can.<br>
<br>
Now, you say &quot;okay, that's soloing, how about grouping?&quot;  The above paragraph shows that a warrior w/o heals is gonna stink up the place for exp, dmg, what have you.  A warrior + a healer of any kind is what most people think of when they say &quot;melee &gt; caster&quot;.  If you throw in a healer for a melee in that equation, think of a wizard with KEI, bard song, and a necro twitching...they're gonna be about the same.  BUT, I say wizards by themselves are overpowered because 1 solo wizard &gt; 1 solo melee of ANY class for exping.<br>
